      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>David Marc is an author, editor, and teacher specializing in communication and mass media.   He earned his PhD in American Studies (Literature, Film, and Communication) from the University of Iowa in 1981.  Since then, he has held adjunct, assistant, or visiting professor positions at Brandeis University, University of California-Los Angeles, the Annenberg School for Communication at the University of Southern California, and the Newhouse School of Public Communication at Syracuse University.  He is the author of a number of books on television and popular culture.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Location Station Owners/Managers Interviews</emph> consists of interviews with eleven owners and/or managers of local televisions stations across the country.  All but one of the interviews were conducted by Marc, usually at the interviewee's home or office.  The context of and reason for the interviews is unknown.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
